        <infon key="n">1</infon>
        <offset>0</offset>
        <text>Ecophysiology of uncultivated marine euryarchaea is linked to particulate organic matter
</text>
      </sentence>
    </passage>
    <passage>
      <offset>89</offset>
      <infon key="type">body</infon>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">2</infon>
        <offset>89</offset>
        <text>Particles in aquatic environments host distinct communities of microbes, yet the evolution of particle-specialized taxa and the extent to which specialized microbial metabolism is associated with particles is largely unexplored.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">3</infon>
        <offset>318</offset>
        <text>Here, we investigate the hypothesis that a widely distributed and uncultivated microbial group--the marine group II euryarchaea (MGII)--interacts with living and detrital particulate organic matter (POM) in the euphotic zone of the central California Current System.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">4</infon>
        <offset>585</offset>
        <text>Using fluorescent in situ hybridization, we verified the association of euryarchaea with POM.
</text>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">5</infon>
        <offset>679</offset>
        <text>We further quantified the abundance and distribution of MGII 16 S ribosomal RNA genes in size-fractionated seawater samples and compared MGII functional capacity in metagenomes from the same fractions.
</text>
        <annotation id="T1">
          <infon key="brat-id">T1</infon>
          <infon key="type">Variable</infon>
          <infon key="brat-type">text-bound</infon>
          <location length="57" offset="881"/>
          <text>The abundance of MGII in free-living and &gt;3 mum fractions</text>
        </annotation>
      </sentence>
      <sentence>
        <infon key="n">6</infon>
        <offset>881</offset>
        <text>The abundance of MGII in free-living and &gt;3 mum fractions decreased with increasing distance from the coast, whereas MGII abundance in the 0.8-3 mum fraction remained constant.
</text>
        <annotation id="T2">
          <infon key="brat-id">T2</infon>
